checkDescription: The number and percent of persons in the CDM that do not have at least one record in the @cdmTableName table
A yes or no value indicating if all fields are present in the @cdmTableName table as expected based on the specification.
The number and percent of records with a NULL value in the @cdmFieldName of the @cdmTableName that is considered not nullable.
A yes or no value indicating if the @cdmFieldName in the @cdmTableName is the expected data type based on the specification.
The number and percent of records that have a duplicate value in the @cdmFieldName field of the @cdmTableName.
The number and percent of records that have a value in the @cdmFieldName field in the @cdmTableName table that does not exist in the @fkTableName table.
The number and percent of records that have a value in the @cdmFieldName field in the @cdmTableName table that do not conform to the @fkDomain domain.
The number and percent of records that have a value in the @cdmFieldName field in the @cdmTableName table that do not conform to the @fkClass class.
The number and percent of records that do not have a standard, valid concept in the @cdmFieldName field in the @cdmTableName table.
The number and percent of records with a NULL value in the @cdmFieldName of the @cdmTableName.
The number and percent of records with a value of 0 in the standard concept field @cdmFieldName in the @cdmTableName table.
The number and percent of records with a value of 0 in the source concept field @cdmFieldName in the @cdmTableName table.
The number and percent of distinct source values in the @cdmFieldName field of the @cdmTableName table mapped to 0.
The number and percent of records with a value in the @cdmFieldName field of the @cdmTableName table less than @plausibleValueLow.
The number and percent of records with a value in the @cdmFieldName field of the @cdmTableName table greater than @plausibleValueHigh.

The number and percent of records with a value in the @cdmFieldName field of the @cdmTableName that occurs prior to the date in the @plausibleTemporalAfterFieldName field of the @plausibleTemporalAfterTableName table.
If yes, the number and percent of records with a date value in the @cdmFieldName field of the @cdmTableName table that occurs after death.
For the combination of CONCEPT_ID @conceptId (@conceptName) and UNIT_CONCEPT_ID @unitConceptId (@unitConceptName), the number and percent of records that have a value less than @plausibleValueLow.
For the combination of CONCEPT_ID @conceptId (@conceptName) and UNIT_CONCEPT_ID @unitConceptId (@unitConceptName), the number and percent of records that have a value higher than @plausibleValueHigh.
For a CONCEPT_ID @conceptId (@conceptName), the number and percent of records associated with patients with an implausible gender (correct gender = @plausibleGender).
For a CONCEPT_ID @conceptId (@conceptName), the number and percent of records associated with the wrong domain. Right domain is @cdmTableName. Wrong domain is @wrongDomain
For a CONCEPT_ID @conceptId (@conceptName), the number and percent of records associated with an implausible value for @cdmValueFieldName (plausible values = @plausibleValues)
For a CONCEPT_ID @conceptId (@conceptName), the number and percent of records that are associated with the wrong unit. Right unit is defined in the concept_relationship table
For a CONCEPT_ID @conceptId (@conceptName), the number and percent of records that are associated with a non-conventional value. These values are defined in the concept_relationship table

For a field @cdmFieldName, the number and percent of records that use a non-conventional concept_id that seems to map to a conventional id. This is defined as being less than @similarityThresholdLevenshtein away using Levenshtein distance or more than @similarityThresholdJaccard percent similar using Jaccard similarity.
For a field @cdmFieldName, the number and percent of records that use a non-conventional concept_id. These conventions are defined in the concept_relationship table
For table @cdmTableName, the number and percent of records that overlap with another record using @startDateField and @endDateField
For the treatment_line table, check if the treatment line number increases over time
For table @cdmTableName, the number and percent of records that have a @cdmFieldName not within one of the observation periods of that patient
For table @cdmTableName, check if periods @startDateField - @endDateField are within the interval @lowerBoundary - @upperBoundary
For table @cdmTableName, the amount and % of records that have a null value for drug_era_end_date, but are not the ongoing regimen.
For table @cdmTableName, the amount and % of records where the treatment line start doesn't correspond to the minimum value of the drug_era starts.
